\pnlcltr\pnstart1 {\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl9\pnlcrm\pnstart1 }\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\b\fs28 Douglas W. Sjoquist\tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab }{\fs24 dwSjoquist@sunetos.com
\par }{\b\fs28 Sunetos, Inc.}{\fs24 \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab \tab www.sunetos.com
\par }\pard \fi720\li6480\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\fs24 October 15, 2000
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\adjustright {\b\fs24 Summary }{\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\adjustright \b\v {\tc {\b\fs24 Summary \tcl3}}}{\b\fs24 
\par }{\fs24 \sect }\sectd \sbknone\linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl {\*\pnseclvl1\pnstart1\pnindent936 }{\*\pnseclvl2\pnstart1\pnindent936 }{\*\pnseclvl3\pnstart1\pnindent936 }{\*\pnseclvl4\pnstart1\pnindent936 }{\*\pnseclvl5\pnstart1\pnindent936 }{\*\pnseclvl6
\pnstart1\pnindent936 }{\*\pnseclvl7\pnstart1\pnindent936 }{\*\pnseclvl8\pnstart1\pnindent936 }{\*\pnseclvl9\pnlcrm\pnstart1\pnindent936 }\pard\plain \li936\nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\fs24 
Experienced system architect with excellent analysis, design and development skills. Strong background with distributed system design and development on both the Java and Win32 platforms.  Rapid problem analysis with the ability to work with users in deve
l
oping and refining requirements. Good grasp of how each piece fits in with organization's overall goals and needs. Extensive experience with object oriented design and development. Ability to learn and integrate new development techniques, tools, and skil
ls quickly, soon becoming productive in the new environment.
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\adjustright {\fs24 
\par }{\b\fs24 Project Experience }{\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\adjustright \b\v {\tc {\b\fs24 Project Experience \tcl3}}}{\b\fs24 
\par }\pard \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\tx720\adjustright {\fs24 \tab }{\b\fs24 WRM-CA, War Reserve Materiel Capability Assessment (1999-2000) }{\pard\plain \fi-720\li720\nowidctlpar\tx720\adjustright \b\v {\tc {\b\fs24 
WRM-CA, War Reserve Materiel Capability Assessment (1999-2000) \tcl4}}}{\b\fs24 
\par }{\fs24 \sect }\sectd \sbknone\linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \li936\nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\fs24 System architect and lead developer for this distributed component system.  The server layers are built on Allaire\rquote 
s Enterprise Java Beans 
(EJB 1.1) server, JRun, with an Oracle database used for persistence and Java Message Service (JMS) used for automatic notification of clients and users.  The primary client interface is pure Java using Swing components.  Portions of the server components
 are also accessible through a CORBA interface to provide a link with UTC-DT and other non-Java clients.
\par }\pard \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\b\fs24 CBP, Collaborative Beddown Planner (1999-2000)}{\fs24 CORBA (Common Object Request Broker Architecture) developer for this distributed component s
ystem.  A CORBA interface was added to an existing Win32 application (Delphi) to use it as a server component in this system built on an EJB architecture. }{\b\fs24  }{\pard\plain \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright \b\v {\tc {\b\fs24 
CBP, Collaborative Beddown Planner (1999-2000)
\par \sect }\sectd \sbknone\linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \li936\nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\fs24 CORBA (Common Object Request Broker Architecture) developer for this distributed component system.  A CORBA interface was added to an exist
ing Win32 application (Delphi) to use it as a server component in this system built on an EJB architecture. 
\par }\pard \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\b\fs24  \tcl4}}}\pard\plain \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\b\fs24 ALA, Air Logistics Application (1998-1999)
\par }{\fs24 \sect }\sectd \sbknone\linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \li936\nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\fs24 
CORBA and Java developer for this distributed component system.  A CORBA interface was added to an existing Win32 application (Delphi) to use it as a server component in this system built on a Java/CORBA architecture. 
\par }\pard \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\b\fs24  }{\pard\plain \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright \b\v {\tc {\b\fs24  \tcl4}}}{\b\fs24 UTC-DT, Unit Type Code Development and Tailoring (1996-1999)
\par }{\fs24 \sect }\sectd \sbknone\linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \li936\nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\fs24 System architect and developer of this peer to peer system.  UTC\_
DT automates the initial generation of equipment requirements based on user defined rules and enables individuals to tailor those requirements.  It uses a custom peer\_to\_
peer socket communication protocol developed for this project to allow multiple users across a LAN or the Internet to view and update the same detailed informat
ion. After the initial data load, only the changes to the data are sent around the network to reduce the bandwidth requirements.
\par }\pard \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\b\fs24 Client/server system for secure database access (1995-1996) }{\pard\plain \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright \b\v {\tc {\b\fs24 Client/server system for secure database access (1995-1996) \tcl4}}}{\b\fs24 
\par }{\fs24 \sect }\sectd \sbknone\linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \li936\nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\fs24 Developed this system using local and server databases and the Novell SDK to run continuously and monitor various directories on the 
network for transaction files to update secure database files. The client programs include book rental and sales, dormitory checkout, and secure network requests for information from the administrative database such as transcripts and account information.

\par }\pard \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\b\fs24 Distributed requisition entry and approval system (1992) }{\pard\plain \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright \b\v {\tc {\b\fs24 Distributed requisition entry and approval system (1992) \tcl4}}}{\b\fs24 
\par }{\fs24 \sect }\sectd \sbknone\linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \li936\nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\fs24 Developed th
is system for a client to allow departments to enter, maintain, and track their own requisitions. It used a rule based system to calculate and then track the necessary approvals required before a purchase order would be created.
\par }\pard \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\b\fs24 Novell tools and utilities (1993-1996) }{\pard\plain \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright \b\v {\tc {\b\fs24 Novell tools and utilities (1993-1996) \tcl4}}}{\b\fs24 
\par }{\fs24 \sect }\sectd \sbknone\linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \li936\nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\fs24 
Developed many tools and utilities for Cedarville to support their 1200+ station campus network and provide an integrated user experience prior to and during the growth of the World Wide Web.
\par }\pard \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright {\b\fs24 Unidata tools (1989-1996) }{\pard\plain \li720\nowidctlpar\adjustright \b\v {\tc {\b\fs24 Unidata tools (1989-1996) \tcl4}}}{\b\fs24 
\par }{\fs24 \sect }\sectd \sbknone\linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \li936\nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20 {\fs24 Developed query tools, import/export tools, and other utilities that were released to the public domain.  These popular tools have been wi
dely used by UniData RDBMS users with great success to leverage their systems.
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\adjustright {\fs24 
\par }{\b\fs24 Design experience }{\pard\plain \nowidctlpar\adjustright \b\v {\tc {\b\fs24 Design experience \tcl3}}}{\b\fs24 
